<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Feasibility evaluation of a DOS to SNES port?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12336&amp;p=140526#p140526"><![CDATA[
Tepples is talking about tile size, like how on the NES everything wants to be a multiple of at least 8x8, but often 16x16 or 32x32.<br />Framebuffer-like systems, such as the VGA's graphics modes, don't really have a constraint on what size tiles they use, including &quot;no tiles at all&quot;, whereas things made for the SNES will be much more annoying if they're not a multiple of 8x8.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Tue Feb 03, 2015 5:33 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
